'''Agrarian National Party''' (in [[Spanish language|Spanish]]: ''Partido Nacional Agrario'') was a [[political party]] in [[Peru]]. It was founded in 1930 by [[Pedro Beltrán Espantoso]], Gerardo Klinge and Manuel González Olaechea.
